        "text": "The exact BASF part numbers that meet your specifications for a 30% glass fiber-reinforced PA66 with enhanced hydrolysis resistance for automotive cooling circuits are:\n\n* **Ultramid® A3HG6 HR** (Commonly ordered in black as SKU: **A3HG6 HR BK23591**)\n* **Ultramid® A3WG6 HRX** (Commonly ordered in black as SKU: **A3WG6 HRX BK23591**)\n\n**Breakdown of the nomenclature:**\n* **A:** Polyamide 66 (PA66) base resin\n* **3:** Medium viscosity (Standard injection molding grade) \n* **H / W:** Heat stabilized\n* **G6:** 30% glass fiber reinforced\n* **HR / HRX:** Hydrolysis Resistant / Enhanced Hydrolysis Resistance\n\nBoth grades are explicitly designed by BASF for high-stress applications in vehicle cooling systems, such as radiator end caps, thermostats, and water containers. The **HRX** variant is often preferred for newer platforms as it offers the highest tier of optimized long-term performance against heat aging and aggressive water/glycol mixtures.",
